label.value: new shoot system emerging from ground in later growth cycle

definition.value: A PO:'vegetative bud' (PO:0000058) that is participating in a GO:'bud dormancy process' (GO:0097207).
A PO:'vegetative bud' (PO:0000058) that is not participating in a GO:'bud dormancy process' (GO:0097207).
A 'non-dormant leaf bud' (PPO:0001010) that is in the 'bud swell stage' (PO:0025531).
A 'non-dormant leaf bud' (PPO:0001010) that is in the 'bud burst stage' (PO:0025532).
If a breaking leaf bud is present, it implies that a new shoot system and unfolding true leaf are also present and observable, hence the “subclass of” axiom.
A 'vascular leaf' (PO:0009025) that is not a 'cotyledon' (PO:0020030).
A 'expanding true leaf' (PPO:0001022) that is in the 'vascular leaf unfolding stage' (PPO:0007005).
A 'true leaf' (PPO:0001013) that is in the 'vascular leaf expanding unfolded stage' (PPO:0007006) or 'vascular leaf post-expansion stage' (PO:0001053) or 'vascular leaf senescent stage' (PO:0001054).
A 'unfolded true leaf' (PPO:0001015) that is in the 'vascular leaf expanding unfolded stage' (PPO:0007006) or 'vascular leaf post-expansion stage' (PO:0001053).
A 'unfolded true leaf' (PPO:0001015) that is in the 'vascular leaf senescent stage' (PO:0001054).
A 'non-senescing unfolded true leaf' (PPO:0001016) that is in the 'vascular leaf expanding unfolded stage' (PPO:0007006) or 'vascular leaf expanded immature stage' (PPO:0007007).
A 'non-senescing unfolded true leaf' (PPO:0001016) that is in the 'vascular leaf mature stage' (PPO:0007008).
A 'expanding true leaf' (PPO:0001022) that is in the 'vascular leaf expanding unfolded stage' (PPO:0007006).
A 'immature unfolded true leaf' (PPO:0001018) that is in the 'vascular leaf expanded immature stage' (PPO:0007007).
A 'true leaf' (PPO:0001013) that is in the 'vascular leaf expansion stage' (PO:0001052).
A 'plant structure' (PO:0009011) that is either a 'reproductive shoot system' (PO:0025082) or a 'fruit' (PO:0009001).
A 'seed' (PO:0009010) that has participated in a 'seed maturation stage' (PO:0007632).
A 'floral structure' (PPO:0001025) that has completed 'floral organ senescence' (GO:0080187).

A 'flower' (PO:0009046) in which all the petaloid floral organs (PO:0025395) have not completed 'floral organ senescence' (GO:0080187). Petaloid floral organs generally are the petals, sepal, or tepals, but may also be floral bracts or petaloid anthers (PO:0009066).  For scoring phenology in grasses, petaloid floral organs can include 'lemma' (PO:0009037), 'palea' (PO:0009038) or 'glume' (PO:0009039), even though a 'glume' (PO:0009039) is not strictly a 'floral organ' (PO:0025395), because it encloses an 'inflorescence' (PO:0009049).
A 'non-senesced flower' (PPO:0001031) that is in the 'unopened flower stage' (PPO:0007009).
A 'non-senesced flower' (PPO:0001031) that is in the 'open flower stage' (PPO:0007010).
An 'open flower' (PPO:0001033) that is in the 'pollen-releasing flower stage' (PPO:0007011).

A 'flower' (PO:0009046) in which all of the petaloid floral organs (PO:0025395) have completed 'floral organ senescence' (GO:0080187). Petaloid floral organs generally are the petals, sepal, or tepals, but may also be floral bracts or petaloid anthers (PO:0009066).  For scoring phenology in grasses, petaloid floral organs can include 'lemma' (PO:0009037), 'palea' (PO:0009038) or 'glume' (PO:0009039), even though a 'glume' (PO:0009039) is not strictly a 'floral organ' (PO:0025395), because it encloses an 'inflorescence' (PO:0009049).
An 'inflorescence' (PO:0009049) with at least one 'non-senesced flower' (PPO:0001031). In the case of an 'unopened flower head' (PPO:0001037), the non-senesced flower(s) might not be visible.
A 'non-senesced flower head' (PPO:0001036) in which all flowers are unopened flowers (PPO:0001032). The unopened flowers might not yet be visible.
A 'non-senesced flower head' (PPO:0001036) with at least one 'open flower' (PPO:0001033).
An 'open flower head' (PPO:0001038) with at least one 'pollen-releasing flower' (PPO:0001034).
An 'inflorescence' (PO:0009049) on which there are no remaining non-senesced flowers (PPO:0001031).
A 'simple fruit or compound fruit' (PPO:0001042) that is in the PO:'fruit ripening stage' (PO:0025502).
A 'ripening fruit' (PPO:0001043) that is in the 'fruit unripe stage' (PPO:0007012).
A 'ripening fruit' (PPO:0001043) that is in the 'fruit ripe stage' (PPO:0007013).
A 'microsporangiate strobilus' (PO:0005031) that has not yet completed the 'pollen-releasing strobilus stage' (PPO:0007016).
A 'fresh pollen cone' (PPO:0001046) that is in the 'open microsporangiate strobilus stage' (PPO:0007015).
A 'open pollen cone' (PPO:0001047) that is in the 'pollen-releasing strobilus stage' (PPO:0007016).
A 'megasporangiate strobilus' (PO:0005032) that has not yet been abscised and has not yet releases all of its seeds.
A 'fresh seed cone' (PPO:0001049) that is in the 'megasporangiate strobilus ripening stage' (PPO:0007017).
A 'ripening seed cone' (PPO:0001050) that is in the 'megasporangiate strobilus unripe stage' (PPO:0007018).
A 'ripening seed cone' (PPO:0001050) that is in the 'megasporangiate strobilus ripe stage' (PPO:0007019).

A PO:'plant structure' (PO:0009011) that is not a whole organism; i.e. a proper part of a PO:'whole plant' (PO:0000003).  Note that a 'portion of a plant' need no longer be physically part of the 'whole plant' from which it originated (e.g., a  herbarium specimen).

A PATO:'quality' (PATO:0000001) of a 'portion of a plant' (PPO:0001053) or a 'whole plant' (PO:0000003) that provides phenologically relevant information about the 'portion of a plant' or the 'whole plant'.
A 'plant phenological trait' (PPO:0002000) that is measured by the number of some 'plant structure' (PO:0009011) that are part of a 'whole plant' (PO:0000003).
The number can be 0 or more.

A 'plant phenological trait' (PPO:0002000) that is measured by the number of some 'plant structure' (PO:0009011) that a 'whole plant' (PO:0000003) has abscised or that have been removed from a 'whole plant' (PO:0000003).
The number can be 0 or more.
